*.md text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
LICENSE text eol=lf

# Codex hook PowerShell scripts are UTF-8 WITH BOM and must round-trip
# byte-faithfully (Windows PowerShell 5.1 misparses BOM-less non-ASCII .ps1).
# -text disables EOL normalization so the bytes (BOM + LF) survive clone /
# checkout unchanged, regardless of the user's core.autocrlf setting (#1502).
*.ps1 -text
